.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "Holberton School" "Simple Shell Project"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- a simple UNIX command line interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simple_shell
.br
.B ./hsh

.SH DESCRIPTION
simple_shell is a basic UNIX command line interpreter.
It reads commands from standard input and executes them.

The shell works in both interactive and non-interactive modes.
It uses fork and execve to execute commands.

.SH FEATURES
Display a prompt and wait for user input.
Execute commands with arguments.
Search executables using the PATH environment variable.
Implement built-in commands such as exit and env.
Handle end of file (EOF).

.SH BUILTINS
.TP
.B exit
Exit the shell.
.TP
.B env
Print the current environment.

.SH ENVIRONMENT
The shell uses the PATH environment variable to locate executables.

.SH RETURN VALUE
simple_shell returns 0 on success.

.SH AUTHORS
See AUTHORS file.

.SH SEE ALSO
sh(1)
